The following is a list of Philippine television ratings for '''2010''' coming from [[Kantar Media Philippines|Kantar Media]]. '''(To be populated)'''
== Markets == {{see|Kantar Media Philippines}} Kantar Media uses a nationwide panel size of 2,609 urban and rural homes. Audience panel covers and represents 100% of the total Philippine TV viewing population. It has a total of 6.315 million homes in rural areas and 8.820 million homes in urban areas across the Philippines, bringing the total TV universe to 15.135 million homes nationwide covering 75 million individuals.
Kantar Media was created on early 2009 to established television audience measurement in the entire Philippines, that covers 100% both rural and urban areas. Kantar Media also has seven sectors: [[National Capital Region]], [[Mega Manila|Suburbs]], [[Northern Luzon|North Luzon]], [[Central Luzon]], [[Southern Tagalog|South Luzon]], [[Visayas]] and [[Mindanao]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://lionheartv.net/2012/02/facts-about-agb-neilsen-and-kantar.html |title=Archived copy |access-date=2013-04-20 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130703065143/http://lionheartv.net/2012/02/facts-about-agb-neilsen-and-kantar.html |archive-date=2013-07-03 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref>
