{{Infobox VG | title = Massive Assault Network 2 | image = Massive Assault Network 2 Cover.jpg | caption = | developer = | publisher = [[Wargaming.net]] | series = ''[[Massive Assault (series)|Massive Assault]]'' | engine = | released = 2006 | genre = [[Turn-based tactics]] | modes = [[Single player]], [[Multiplayer]] | platforms = [[Microsoft Windows]] }}
'''''Massive Assault Network 2''''' is a [[massively multiplayer online game]] published by [[wargaming.net]]. The game is a turn-based futuristic military simulation. The game is science fiction and takes place in the future, with the Free States Union vying for power against the Phantom League. Opponents square off against each other on a particular planet and fight to control all of its nations. Each player is given secret ally nations, and each nation has a limited amount of resources for building units.<ref>Aceinet, [http://pc.gamezone.com/gzreviews/r28163.htm Massive Assault Network 2 Review] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080311052202/http://pc.gamezone.com/gzreviews/r28163.htm |date=2008-03-11 }}, ''GameZone'', December 14, 2006, Accessed March 23, 2008</ref> The game comes in both a free and subscription version. The free version provides full unit set and one level, where the subscription version provides access to several levels.<ref>Fudge, James, [http://uk.pc.gamespy.com/pc/massive-assault-network/506248p1.html Massive Assault Network Launched (PC)], ''GameSpy'', April 13, 2004, Accessed March 23, 2008</ref>
