{{Infobox person | name = Mie Nanamori | image = | caption = | native_name = 七森 美江 | native_name_lang = ja | birth_name = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1972|10|16}} | birth_place = [[Tokyo]], Japan | nationality = Japanese | other_names = | alias = | death_date = | education = | occupation = Actress, ''tarento'' | years_active = | agent = {{ubl|Sadeeca|Cross Point<ref name="profile">{{cite book|title=[[Nihon Tarento Meikan|Nihon Tarento Meikan 2016]]|publisher=VIP Times|date=27 Jan 2016|page=661}}</ref>}} | known_for = | home_town = | height = 1.68 m (2003) | spouse = | relatives = | death_place = | children = | awards = | website = }} {{nihongo|'''Mie Nanamori'''|七森 美江|Nanamori Mie|born 16 October 1972, in [[Tokyo]], Japan}}<ref name="profile"/> is a Japanese former actress and ''tarento''. She was represented with Sadeeca.
==Biography== Nanamori was born in 1972{{efn|As a race queen her year of birth was 1974, other profiles said it was 1975.}} in Tokyo.
She made her debut after she became a race queen for the '' '97 [[Suntory|Suntory Nama Beer]] Campaign Girl'' and ''Kamome Service''. Nanamori appeared in ''Shutsudō! Minisuka Police'' as the second and third generation Minisuka Police in January 1997, and later on October she became a "Won Girl" in the [[Tokyo Broadcasting System]] series ''Wonderful''. She appeared in the series until March of the following year.
Nanamori worked as an actress in television dramas and advertisements and played Rose Monster Ru-Baruba-De in ''[[Kamen Rider Kuuga]]'' in 2000 and Lisa Teagle (Deka Bright) in ''[[Tokusou Sentai Dekaranger]]'' in 2004, whom she played as a cool woman. She was belonged to the talent agency Sadeeca until 2003 and she is later retired from her career. Nanamori is now married and has a child.
==Filmography==
