{{Infobox video game| title = Offroad Legends |image = |developer =DogByte Games |publisher =DogByte Games |designer = |engine =[[Horde3D (game engine)|Horde3D]] |released =June 2012 |genre = [[Racing video game|Racing]] |modes = Single player |platforms = [[iOS]], [[Android (operating system)|Android]], Xperia Play }}
'''Offroad Legends''' is a series of [[racing game|racing]] [[video game]]s which utilize pseudo-3D graphics released initially in 2012 for mobile platforms.<ref>{{cite web |url =http://www.gamespot.com/offroad-legends/ |title =Offroad Legends |website =gamespot.com |publisher =GameSpot |accessdate =2014-01-24 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url =http://www.gamefaqs.com/iphone/675444-offroad-legends |title =Offroad Legends |website =gamefaqs.com |publisher =GameFAQs |accessdate =2014-01-24 }}</ref>
== Gameplay == The mechanics of the game involve off-road racing in various all-terrain vehicles. The game also features high-definition 3D graphics as a result of being built with the [[Horde3D (game engine)|Horde3D]] engine.<ref>http://download.cnet.com/Offroad-Legends-Sahara/3000-20416_4-75812622.html</ref> The underlying engine allows for vehicle and terrain deformation and also has retina display for [[iOS]].<ref>http://apps.usatoday.com/#iphone/offroad-legends/id/516875543</ref>
== Sequels == * ''Offroad Legends: Sahara'': is a [[free-to-play]] sequel to the original due to its positive reception.<ref>{{cite web |url =http://toucharcade.com/2012/11/27/ta-plays-offroad-legends-sahara-a-visually-solid-stunt-car-game/ |title =TA Plays: 'Offroad Legends Sahara' - A Visually Solid Stunt Car Game |last =Nicholson |first =Brad |date =November 27, 2012 |website =toucharcade.com |publisher =toucharcade |accessdate =2014-01-24 }}</ref> * ''Offroad Legends: Warmup'': is the latest in the series released in December 2013.<ref>{{cite web |url =https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/offroad-legends-warmup/id541878076?mt=8 |title =Offroad Legends Warmup |website =itunes.com |publisher =Apple |accessdate =2014-01-24 }}</ref>
== Reception == The game has received fairly positive reviews since its release. slide to Play gives the game a 3 out of 4 stating it builds off of solid mobile racing mechanics.<ref>http://www.slidetoplay.com/review/offroad-legends-review/</ref> modojo has also given the game a positive review <ref>http://gamingnuts.com/offroad-legends/</ref> because of its solid gameplay and well performing mechanics.<ref>http://www.modojo.com/reviews/offroad_legends</ref> PocketGamer gave a less than average review of the game stating poor level design giving the game a rating of 7/10.<ref>http://www.pocketgamer.co.uk/r/iPad/Offroad+Legends/review.asp?c=47176</ref> The game has a Metascore of 76 based on 4 critics.<ref>http://www.metacritic.com/game/ios/offroad-legends</ref> The game currently holds a 76.25% on GameRankings.<ref>http://www.gamerankings.com/iphone/675444-offroad-legends/index.html</ref>
== External links == {{Official website|http://www.dogbytegames.com/}}
